iter=48: Enabled adaptive phase locking by default -> score=72.37 (was 72.93), reverted. Complex mix streaming TP 100->62.5, streaming avg dropped 70.67->69.50.
iter=49: Sqrt scaling on streaming hybrid crossfade -> score=72.81 (was 72.93), reverted. Sine speedup streaming SC worsened, transient-heavy unchanged.
iter=50: Changed default window from BlackmanHarris to Hann -> score=69.14 (was 72.93450093269348), reverted. SC/LSD worsened across all cases, BH sidelobe suppression is important.
iter=51: Replaced start mirror padding with zero padding in PV -> score=72.67 (was 72.93), reverted. TP=50% cases unchanged, complex mix streaming TP dropped 100->87.5.
iter=52: Switched default crossfade from Fixed(0.012) to Adaptive -> score=72.93 (was 72.93), no change. Adaptive computes same crossfade as fixed for these test signals, reverted.
iter=53: Ratio-scaled PV start+end padding (fft_size/ratio warmup) -> score=69.94 (was 72.93), reverted. Sine speedup TP 100->0, complex stream TP 100->87.5. End pad increase for ratio<1 caused spectral degradation.
iter=54: Increased PV start_pad_mult to 16 for ratio<0.85 -> score=72.29 (was 72.93), reverted. Longer mirror pad worsened SC (phase interference), vocal slowdown -1.3, sine stream -7.
iter=55: Increased WSOLA_SEARCH_MS_SMALL 10->14, relaxed search clamp seg_size/2->seg_size*3/4 -> score=71.49 (was 72.93), reverted. Larger search caused temporal drift in WSOLA.
iter=56: Reduced WSOLA overlap from segment_size/2 to segment_size/3 for far-from-unity -> score=71.87 (was 72.93), reverted. Less overlap caused spectral artifacts at boundaries.
iter=57: Phase reset at mirror boundary frame + 5ms end fade-out in PV -> score=69.31 (was 72.93), reverted. Phase reset killed sine speedup TP 100->0 (synthesis discontinuity at reset), fade-out removed real onset.
iter=58: Reduced streaming crossfade delta cap from 3/4 to 1/2 -> score=72.88 (was 72.93664503097534), reverted. Sine slowdown streaming SC dropped 92.3->90.5, other streaming scores unchanged.
iter=59: Disabled HPSS and multi-resolution (plain PV for tonal) -> score=63.90 (was 72.93664503097534), reverted. Transient-heavy cases collapsed (SC=14-34%, TP=0-90%). PV smears percussive content without HPSS separation.
iter=60: Increased PHASE_GRADIENT_BLEND from 0.15 to 0.25 -> score=72.80 (was 72.93664503097534), reverted. Complex mix SC/LSD worsened, overall marginal degradation from over-smoothed phase.
iter=61: Added hpss_min_len=fft_size*4 to skip HPSS for short tonal segments -> score=72.72 (was 72.93664503097534), streaming avg dropped 70.69->70.25, batch unchanged. Quality inconsistency between early/late streaming chunks. Reverted.
iter=62: Swapped priority: multi_res before HPSS -> score=55.67 (was 72.93664503097534), dramatic quality drop. Multi_res 3-band PV significantly worse than HPSS for tonal segments. Reverted.
iter=63: Reduced PV edge correction: half correction_len, gain cap 4->2, threshold 0.7->0.5 -> score=72.74 (was 72.93664503097534), LSD worsened for transient-heavy cases, TP unchanged. Edge correction is needed. Reverted.
iter=64: Added cosine taper to start mirror padding in PV -> score=72.91 (was 72.93664503097534), TP=50% cases unchanged. Taper doesn't affect onset peaks at 35ms. Reverted.
iter=65: Cosine taper on start mirror padding -> score=72.91 (was 72.93664503097534), TP=50% unchanged. False onset peaks at 35ms from PV mirror boundary phase reversal; at end from truncation. Not fixable with simple mirror taper. Reverted.
iter=66: Per-window edge correction (gain 12x, 85% threshold) + 64-sample end fade-out -> score=67.16 (was 72.93664503097534), massive regression. Over-aggressive per-window gain amplified artifacts. Reverted.
iter=67: Skip WSOLA for quiet percussive in HPSS (use linear resample when perc_rms < 5% input_rms) -> score=72.62 (was 72.93664503097534), TP=50% cases unchanged, LSD slightly worse for batch tonal. Reverted.
iter=68: Block-wise interpolated edge correction (3.0x max gain, 512-block, 85% target) + 512-sample end fade-out -> score=68.61 (was 72.93664503097534). Sine speedup TP=0%, vocal speedup TP dropped. Block gains amplified artifacts, end fade removed real transients. Reverted.
iter=69: Increased HPSS percussive_width 17->31 -> score=72.76 (was 72.93664503097534), streaming transient-heavy SC worsened. Reverted.
iter=70: 2048-sample cosine fade-in/out for single tonal segments -> score=63.04 (was 72.93664503097534), reverted. TP worse: sine speedup TP 100->0, vocal speedup TP 100->50. SC/LSD degraded. Fades create spectral mismatch at edges.
