iter=79: replaced end edge correction with 2048-sample cosine fade-in/fade-out → score=71.10 (was 73.00), TP unchanged at 50% for affected cases, SC worsened across most cases, vocal speedup batch TP regressed from 100% to 50%. Reverted.
iter=80: Increased WSOLA overlap to 3/4 for extreme ratios (>0.4 from unity) -> score=72.72 (was 73.00), transient-heavy speedup LSD worsened 13.35->17.70, reverted
iter=81: Skip HPSS+multi_res for short tonal segments (< fft_size*5), fall through to plain PV -> score=72.77 (was 73.00), batch unchanged (segments long enough), streaming transient-heavy worsened: SC/LSD/TP all degraded. HPSS helps even for short segments. Reverted.
iter=82: Increased PV start mirror padding from 4x to 8x hop for extreme ratios -> score=70.98 (was 73.00), sine speedup TP collapsed 100->0% (longer mirror masked onset), sine slowdown streaming SC worsened. Longer mirror does more harm than good. Reverted.
iter=83: Disabled HPSS by default (hpss_enabled: false), tonal segments went through multi-resolution PV instead -> score=55.67 (was 73.00101733207703), massive regression. Multi-res path is much worse than HPSS+PV. Reverted.
iter=84: PV-stretch percussive component instead of WSOLA in HPSS tonal path -> score=64.78 (was 73.00101733207703), regression. WSOLA is better than PV for percussive residual. Reverted.
iter=85: Changed default window from BlackmanHarris to Hann -> score=69.77 (was 73.00101733207703), regression. BH's superior sidelobe suppression (-92dB vs Hann's -31dB) is more important than Hann's narrower mainlobe for these test cases. Reverted.
iter=86: Enable dynamic_wsola_search by default -> score=73.00 (was 73.00101733207703), no change at all. WSOLA search range scaling doesn't affect scoring because transient segments use separate WSOLA params. Reverted.
iter=87: Longer PV start mirror padding for slowdown ratios (8x hop instead of 4x when ratio<1) -> score=72.89 (was 73.00101733207703). Sine slowdown streaming SC regressed 92.4->86.2 (more reflected content = more phase mismatch). TP=50% unchanged. Reverted.
iter=88: HPSS mirror padding (pad_frames=harmonic_width/2) -> score=71.27 (was 73.00). Fixed slowdown TP (50->100%) but killed speedup TP (100->0%). Mirror phase artifacts at onset boundary destroyed onset alignment for speedup. Reverted.
iter=89: PV edge correction threshold 0.7->0.5, gain cap 4.0->2.0 -> score=72.88 (was 73.00). TP=50% unchanged, edge correction is NOT the cause. LSD slightly worse for transient-heavy (less genuine correction). Reverted.
