iter=94: Enable adaptive phase locking by default -> score=72.44 (was 73.00), streaming avg worsened 70.80->69.63. Adaptive mode switches disrupted streaming phase coherence. Reverted.
iter=95: Raised sub-bass phase lock cutoff 120->200 Hz -> score=69.70 (was 73.00), both batch and streaming worsened. Too many bins excluded from peak-based phase locking. Reverted.
iter=96: Replaced WSOLA with linear resampling for HPSS percussive component -> score=73.05 (was 73.50), reverted. SC worsened significantly for transient-heavy (49.5->41.3 batch, 58.1->51.9 streaming slowdown). Linear resampling low-pass filters percussive, hurting SC more than helping LSD/TP.
